Combine flour, sugar, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda and salt in a large bowl. Add oats, raisins and pecans; set aside. Beat eggs in a large bowl. Add melted butter, milk and maple flavor. Stir in flour mixture; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake in 350 degrees F. oven 15 minutes per batch. Makes 3 batches.